recipe.title: Classic Spaghetti Bolognese
recipe.ingredients: spaghetti, ground beef, tomato sauce, onion, garlic
recipe.instructions: 1. Cook spaghetti according to package instructions. 2. In a large skillet, brown ground beef with onion and garlic. 3. Add tomato sauce and simmer. 4. Serve sauce over cooked spaghetti.

recipe.title: Creamy Garlic Parmesan Chicken
recipe.ingredients: chicken breasts, garlic, parmesan cheese, heavy cream
recipe.instructions: 1. Season chicken breasts with salt and pepper. 2. In a skillet, cook chicken until golden brown. 3. Add garlic, parmesan cheese, and heavy cream. 4. Simmer until sauce thickens. 5. Serve with your favorite side dish.

recipe.title: Homemade Margherita Pizza
recipe.ingredients: pizza dough, mozzarella cheese, tomato sauce, basil leaves
recipe.instructions: 1. Preheat oven to 450°F. 2. Roll out pizza dough and top with tomato sauce, mozzarella cheese, and basil leaves. 3. Bake for 12-15 minutes or until crust is golden brown. 4. Slice and serve.

recipe.title: Grilled Lemon Herb Salmon
recipe.ingredients: salmon fillets, lemon, garlic, fresh herbs, olive oil
recipe.instructions: 1. Preheat grill to medium-high heat. 2. Season salmon fillets with salt, pepper, lemon juice, garlic, and herbs. 3. Grill for 4-5 minutes per side or until cooked through. 4. Serve with a side of vegetables or salad.

recipe.title: Chocolate Chip Cookies
recipe.ingredients: flour, butter, sugar, chocolate chips, vanilla extract
recipe.instructions: 1. Preheat oven to 375°F. 2. In a mixing bowl, cream together butter and sugar. 3. Add flour, chocolate chips, and vanilla extract. 4. Drop spoonfuls of dough onto a baking sheet. 5. Bake for 10-12 minutes or until golden brown.

recipe.title: Spaghetti Carbonara
recipe.instructions: Cook spaghetti according to package instructions. In a separate pan, cook bacon until crispy. In a bowl, whisk eggs and grated Parmesan cheese. Drain cooked spaghetti and mix with bacon. Pour egg mixture over spaghetti and toss until well coated. Serve hot.

recipe.title: Chicken Curry
recipe.ingredients: Chicken, Curry Powder, Coconut Milk, Onion
recipe.instructions: Heat oil in a pan and sauté onions until translucent. Add chicken pieces and cook until browned. Stir in curry powder and cook for a minute. Pour in coconut milk and simmer until chicken is cooked through. Serve with rice.

recipe.title: Chocolate Chip Cookies
recipe.instructions: Preheat oven to 350°F. In a bowl, cream butter and sugar. Gradually add flour and mix until well combined. Stir in chocolate chips. Drop spoonfuls of dough onto a baking sheet and bake for 10-12 minutes or until golden brown. Allow to cool before serving.

recipe.title: Mushroom Risotto
recipe.ingredients: Arborio Rice, Mushrooms, Onion, Parmesan Cheese
recipe.instructions: In a large saucepan, sauté onions and mushrooms in butter until softened. Add Arborio rice and cook for a minute. Gradually add chicken broth, stirring constantly, until rice is cooked and creamy. Stir in grated Parmesan cheese. Serve hot.

recipe.title: Blueberry Pancakes
recipe.instructions: In a mixing bowl, combine flour, milk, and eggs. Whisk until smooth. Gently fold in blueberries. Heat a non-stick pan and pour a ladleful of batter. Cook until bubbles form on the surface, then flip and cook until golden brown. Serve with maple syrup.

recipe.title: Chicken Curry
recipe.ingredients: Chicken, Curry Powder, Coconut Milk, Onion, Garlic
recipe.instructions: Heat oil in a pan and sauté onions and garlic until fragrant. Add curry powder and cook for a minute. Add chicken pieces and cook until browned. Pour in coconut milk and simmer until chicken is cooked through. Serve with rice.

recipe.instructions: In a large bowl, toss together torn Romaine lettuce, croutons, and grated Parmesan cheese. Drizzle with Caesar dressing and toss until well coated. Serve immediately.

recipe.title: Mushroom Risotto
recipe.ingredients: Arborio Rice, Mushrooms, Onion, Garlic, Parmesan Cheese
recipe.instructions: In a saucepan, heat olive oil and sauté chopped onions and garlic until translucent. Add sliced mushrooms and cook until tender. Stir in Arborio rice and cook for a minute. Gradually add hot vegetable broth, stirring constantly until absorbed. Continue adding broth and stirring until rice is creamy and tender. Serve hot.
